{[%evp 0,28,28,39,44,41,41,46,52,43,54,34,67,79,76,28,72,31,58,-41,-51,-51,-51,
-53,-69,-66,-75,-98,-95,-163,-177] In this chapter we will investigate the
novelty 7.Ne2} 1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nd4 4. Nf3 a6 5. Bd3 {White's main
move here} Nc6 $5 {not a new idea in this variation. After this retreat White
has to justify the position of his light-squared bishop.} 6. O-O g6 (6... e6 {
is another possible set-up}) 7. Ne2 $146 {An interesting new try. White wants
to play c3 followed up by Bc2 and d4 and get a harmonious piece arrangement.} (
{Previously White has mostly tried} 7. Re1 Bg7 8. e5 {but Black has scored
well after} f6 $1) 7... Nb4 $1 {The critical response} 8. Bc4 b5 9. Bxf7+ $5 {
A very curious sacrifice.} ({I suppose White didn't like the position arising
after} 9. Bb3 c4 10. a3 cxb3 11. axb4 bxc2 12. Qxc2 Bb7 {It's complicated, but
Black should be alright.}) 9... Kxf7 10. d4 Bg7 11. d5 a5 12. c3 $2 ({White
should have played} 12. Nf4 $1 Nh6 13. a4 $13 {with interesting compensation.})
12... Na6 13. e5 {Quesada Perez,Y (2523)-Nedev,T (2496) Batumi GEO 2018 After}
Bb7 $146 14. Nf4 Nh6 $17 {White's compensation is not sufficient. Conclusion:
The idea 7.Ne2 is playable and I expect new games in this line in the near
future. In my opinion White should play 12.Nf4 with very interesting play.} *

