60,47,42,14]} 1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 g6 4. f4 Bg7 5. Nf3 ({Surprisingly} 5.
a3 {is gaining more and more popularity. We had two important games in Batumi.}
O-O 6. Nf3 Bg4 {another game saw} (6... Na6 7. e5 Nd7 8. Be3 c5 9. Qd2 cxd4 10.
Bxd4 dxe5 11. fxe5 Ndc5 $2 {Not a good move, however, I don't think Black has
equality here} 12. Qe3 $1 b6 13. O-O-O Qc7 {Tari, A (2618)-Mchedlishvili, M 
(2607) Batumi GEO 2018 White has a lot way for serious advantage, but the most
convincing one seems to be} 14. e6 $1 Nxe6 {or} (14... Bxe6 15. b4) 15. Nd5 Qd6
16. Be5 $1 Qc5 17. Qe4 {and Black cannot avoid material losses.}) 7. h3 Bxf3 8.
Qxf3 e5 $146 {hardly a good novelty.} ({However,} 8... Nc6 9. Be3 e5 10. dxe5
dxe5 11. f5 {hardly promise Black an easy life, either.}) 9. dxe5 dxe5 10. f5
$1 gxf5 11. Qxf5 Ne8 12. Qg4 Nc6 13. Bg5 {and White was clearly better in
