7. Qd4 $5 {Not a surprising move anymore.} O-O 8. Bd2 Nc6 9. Qc4 {This line is
well-known and occured in 29 games already.} Be6 10. Qb5 Qc7 {Recently Black
has been doing well here} 11. O-O-O dxc5 $5 $146 ({Previously Black has tried
only} 11... Rac8 {Villanueva,M (2466)-Nagle,S (2432) chess.com INT 2018 White
should have reacted with} 12. Kb1 {with better chances.}) 12. Qxc5 ({Another
idea for White is} 12. e5 Nd4 13. exf6 $5 Nxb5 14. fxg7 Rfd8 15. Nxb5 Qc8 {
with very interesting imbalanced play.}) 12... b6 13. Qa3 (13. Qe3 {would run
into} Ng4 14. Qe1 Bxc3 15. Bxc3 Qxf4+ 16. Kb1 Rad8 {and Black should be fine
despite losing his dark-squared bishop.}) 13... a5 14. Ng5 (14. e5 Ng4 15. Re1
Rad8 {also promises Black interesting compensation.}) 14... Bg4 15. Re1 {
Pichot,A (2562) -Stremavicius,T (2467) Batumi GEO 2018 Black should definitely
have played} Nb4 $1 16. Qb3 Rad8 {with a very complex tactical position.
Black's compensation shouldn't be underestimated.} *

